Of the two types of scenarios, the pool fire scenario provides the most conservative results for the ACS radius of influence.  Therefore, the radius of influence for this scenario has been used in determining the exposed population and public and environmental receptors for the ACS. 
Prevention Program
The LNG covered process is subject to Program 3 prevention program requirements because it is subject to OSHAA?s PSM standards and is not eligible for Program 1.  The PG&E Program 3 prevention program includes the following:
A?    Process Safety Information;
A?    Process Hazard Review;
A?    Operating Procedures;
A?    Training;
A?    Mechanical Integrity;
A?    Management of Change;
A?    Pre-Startup Safety Review;
A?    Compliance Audits;
A?    Incident Investigations;
A?    Employee Participation;
A?    Hot Work Permit; and
A?    Contractors.
Chemical specific prevention steps include the ESD system as described in Section 2.1.3
The LNG Facility was built to the design standard of NFPA 59A, which is specific to LNG.  In addition, the LNG tank was designed using Zone 4 seismic design standards, even though the facility is in Zone 3, for an added measure of safety.  
Because the SFD will be the responder in the event of an emergency incident involving an LNG fire detect, PG&E conducted a responder orientation exercise with the SFD on March 21, 2008, to familiarize SFD personnel with the facility and the hazards associated with LNG.
